article.headline: Lipscomb 90, North Florida 69
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Michael Lusk scored 21, grabbed 11 rebounds and dished out nine assists to lead Lipscomb to a 90-69 win over North Florida on Saturday in the regular-season finale for both teams. Adnan Hodzic also had 21 points for the Bisons (16-13, 12-9 Atlantic Sun Conference), who won their eighth straight game. Brandon Brown chipped in with 10 points. Lipscomb will host the A-Sun tournament in Nashville, Tenn., which starts on Wednesday. Cortez Riley paced the Ospreys (8-22, 6-14) with 19 points and Matt Sauey added 11. North Florida finished the season on a two-game skid. Lipscomb opened the game on a 16-4 run and led 49-24 at halftime. The Ospreys outscored the Bisons 45-41 in the second half, but it wasn't enough. The Bisons hit 24 free throws in the game, while the Ospreys made just nine.
